

Help! I've using fvwm2 with with FvwmButtons Module and some of the programs 

will no be envoked from thier buttons. I'm guessing this could be a mem stack 

problem?  here is my FvwmButtons config file:



################## FvwmButtons button-bar ################################


*FvwmButtonsGeometry -2+2


*FvwmButtonsBack grey50


*FvwmButtonsColumns 1


*FvwmButtonsPixmap none


*FvwmButtonsPadding 0 0


*FvwmButtons (Size 48 48 Frame 0 Padding 0 0 Swallow xload 'exec xload 

-geometry 48x48 -hl blue -jumpscroll 10 -update 5 -bg grey50 &')


*FvwmButtons (Frame 0 Swallow asclock 'exec asclock -shape -12 &')


*FvwmButtons (Title csh, Icon Monitor.xpm, Action `Exec aterm -title csh &`)


*FvwmButtons (Title "su csh", Icon Computer.xpm, Action `Exec aterm -e su &`)


<bold>*FvwmButtons (Title Imaging, Icon Brush.xpm, Action `Exec display 

&`)</bold>


*FvwmButtons (Title Editor, Icon Publish.xpm, Action `Exec xvile &`)


<bold>*FvwmButtons (Title PPP, Icon interface.xpm, Action `Exec pppd &`)</bold>


*FvwmButtons (Title Web, Icon WWW.xpm, Action `Exec nohup arena &`)


*FvwmButtons (Title Mail, Icon e1.xpm, Action `Exec exmh &`)



Buttons in bold do not work.



